solutions.content:
Three line explanation for interviews

1) Intitate a count variable and Iterate over the matrix 
	* 	Count the island whenever we are encouterning '1' at any index.
	* 	Perform BFS and DFS at the index to make all the neighboring elements from '1' --> '0' as they are part of same island. If the interviewer says we can not mutate the array then maintain a separate mX n visited array and mark all the BFS and DFS elements as visited.
2) For BFS maintain a queue and push index of encountered '1' in queue and subsequently keep adding all the neighbors with value '1' till queue becomes empty.
3) Return the count.

Time Complexity: O(mn) in both BFS and DFS
Space Complexity: O(mn) in BFS as we are maintianing a queue which in worst cases can have all the elements of matrix

You can follow me on https://twitter.com/Jaspind07199761 for DS and Algo tips
or connect on https://www.linkedin.com/in/jaspindersingh1/

**BFS**

```
class Solution {
    public int numIslands(char[][] grid) {
        if(grid == null || grid.length == 0) return 0;
        int count =0;
        int m = grid.length;
        int n = grid[0].length;
        int [][] dirs = new int [][] {{0,1}, {1,0}, {-1,0}, {0,-1}};
        for(int i = 0; i <  m; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == '1'){
                    count++;
                    Queue <int []> q = new LinkedList<>();
                    q.add(new int[] {i,j});
                    grid[i][j] = '0';
                    while(!q.isEmpty()){
                        int [] curr = q.poll();
                        for(int [] dir : dirs){
                            int r = curr[0] + dir[0];
                            int c = curr[1] + dir[1];
                            if(r >= 0 && r < m && c >= 0 && c < n && grid[r][c] == '1'){
                                 q.add(new int[] {r,c});
                                 grid[r][c] = '0';
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```


