I was searching for a better solution to the LIS problem and I came across this. I found it fascinating and it's easy to implement. Using tree set avoids the need to implement your own binary search which can be error prone during a high stress interview.
```
	public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        TreeSet<Integer> t = new TreeSet<>();
        for (int x: nums) {
            Integer c = t.ceiling(x);
            if (c != null) {
                t.remove(c);
            }
            t.add(x);
        }
        return t.size();
    }
```

