// 既然题目提示我们这题的时间复杂度可以优化到 O(nlogn)
// Since the question suggests that the time complexity of this question can be optimized to O(nlogn)
// logn 的复杂度只有二分法能办到了
// The complexity can only be achieved by dichotomy.
// 我们把这些数分成许多堆, 按照下面定义的规则:
// We divide these numbers into many piles, according to the rules defined below:
// 1. 依次从数组中拿出一个数, 首先第一个数就放在第 1 个堆就行
// 1. Take a number from the array in turn, and put the first number on the first pile.
// 2. 之后每次取出的数必须放在所有堆顶的不小于它的数上面
// 2. After that, the number taken out each time must be placed on top of all the numbers at the top of the pile that are not less than it.
// 3. 如果有多个堆顶的数都不小于它, 就放在最靠左边的堆上面
// 3. If the number at the top of multiple piles is not less than it, put it on the leftmost pile.
// 4. 如果没有这样的堆, 就从右边新起一个堆放
// 4. If there is no such pile, start a new one on the right.
// 这个规则的限制下, 所有堆顶的元素从左到右始终都是有序的
// Under the restriction of this rule, all the elements at the top of the piles are always ordered from left to right.
// 这样我们就可以应用二分搜索, 来找第 1 个堆顶的数不小于待放数的堆了
// In this way, we can use binary search to find the first pile, and the number at the top of it is not less than the number waiting to be placed.
// 那么这和我们的问题: 寻找最长递增子序列有什么关系呢？
// So what does this have to do with our question: finding the longest increasing subsequence?
// 可以证明, 最长递增子序列就是堆的个数
// It can be proved that the longest increasing subsequence is the number of piles.
int lengthOfLIS(vector<int>& nums)
{
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<int> pilesTop;
    // 最多分了 n 个堆, 我们提前分配空间提升效率
	// There are no more than n piles, so we allocate space in advance to improve efficiency.
    pilesTop.reserve(n);
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        // 寻找左边界二分搜索
		// Search for left boundary
        auto left = lower_bound(pilesTop.begin(), pilesTop.end(), nums[i]);
        // 如果没有找到合适的堆, 独自放在最右边
		// If you don't find a suitable pile, put it on the far right alone.
        if(left == pilesTop.end())
            pilesTop.push_back(nums[i]);
        // 否则, 放堆顶上
		// Otherwise, put it on top of the pile.
        else
            *left = nums[i];
    }
    return pilesTop.size();
}
