**DP + Tabulation (Easy): `O(n2) / O(n)`**
*In tabulation we create our own order.*
```
    public static int[] dp;
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        dp = new int[nums.length + 1];
        Arrays.fill(dp, 1);
        int chain = 1;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < i; j++)
                if(nums[i] > nums[j]) {
                    dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1);
                    chain = Math.max(chain, dp[i]);
                }
        }

        return chain;
    }
```
**Binary search (Easy): `O(n*log(n)) / O(1)`**
*Insert and update the value if sequence in possible till that position.*
```
    public static int[] dp;
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        dp = new int[nums.length];
        int chain = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            int l = 0, r = chain;

            while(l != r) {
                int m = l + (r - l) / 2;

                if(dp[m] < nums[i])
                    l = m + 1;
                else
                    r = m;
            }

            dp[l] = nums[i];
            if(l == chain) chain++;
        }

        return chain;
    }
```
