solutions.content:
### Brute Force
```
class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        return lengthOfLISFrom(nums, 0, -1);
    }

    private int lengthOfLISFrom(int[] nums, int currentIndex, int previousIndex) {
        if (currentIndex == nums.length)
            return 0;

        int lis = 0;
        if (previousIndex == -1 
            || nums[currentIndex] > nums[previousIndex]) {
            lis = 1 + lengthOfLISFrom(nums, currentIndex + 1, currentIndex);
        }

        lis = Math.max(lis, lengthOfLISFrom(nums, currentIndex + 1, previousIndex));
        return lis;
    }
}
```
### Top-down DP
To overcome overlapping subproblems, we apply memoization:
```
class Solution {
    private Integer[][] dp;
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        dp = new Integer[nums.length][nums.length + 1];
        return lengthOfLISFrom(nums, 0, -1);
    }

    private int lengthOfLISFrom(int[] nums, int currentIndex, int previousIndex) {
        if (currentIndex == nums.length)
            return 0;

        if (dp[previousIndex + 1][currentIndex] != null)
            return dp[previousIndex + 1][currentIndex];

        int lis = 0;
        if (previousIndex == -1 
            || nums[currentIndex] > nums[previousIndex]) {
            lis = 1 + lengthOfLISFrom(nums, currentIndex + 1, currentIndex);
        }

        lis = Math.max(lis, lengthOfLISFrom(nums, currentIndex + 1, previousIndex));

        return dp[previousIndex + 1][currentIndex] = lis;
    }
}
```
### Bottom-up DP
If the number at `currentIndex` is bigger than the number at `previousIndex`, we increment the count for LIS up to the `currentIndex`.

But if there is a bigger LIS without including the number at `currentIndex`, we take that instead.

So we need to find all the increasing subsequences for the number at index `i` and pick the longest one.
```
class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length == 0)
            return 0;

        int[] dp = new int[nums.length];
        dp[0] = 1;

        int maxLength = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) { 
            dp[i] = 1; 
            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) { 
                if (nums[i] > nums[j] && dp[i] <= dp[j]) {
                    dp[i] = dp[j] + 1;  
                    maxLength = Math.max(maxLength, dp[i]);
                }
            }
        }

        return maxLength;
    }
}
```

