# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
### Well this approach is simple and clear also inspired from striver's dp series

### if we can get recursive solution we can memorise it very easily so lets focus on that 

### Here for every element on each index we have two options we can either take it or leave it ,
### if we pick it - curr index becomes prev and curr index moves to next element
### if we dont pick it - prev remains as it is and we move curr index
### but we have a constraint that it has to be increasing subsequence whose condition you find in else if staement where the  current element if picked it must greater than previous element

### it is pretty simple and straight foward right but here it is twisted slightly where we have and extra condition where prev and curr_index are on same element 
 ### in that case,
### if we pick it the current index becomes prev and we move foward to next element (no change)

### but if we dont pick we have to move curr and prev index to next bcz we still dont have prev element (this is a big catch) just think of a scenario that  we can start our subsequence from any index not neccesarily from first index and we have no prev element if we dont pick the starting element so just to keep it sync with current index we increment it until an element is picked.
### so in final if curr index== prev index 
### we have not yet picked any element.

#### hope you find this helpful and this is my first solution post on leetcode

### Thank You and Upvote if u find this helpful.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLIS(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n,vector<int>(n,-1));
        return f(0,0,n,nums,dp);
    }

  int f(int i,int prev,int n,vector<int>& nums,vector<vector<int>>&dp)
  {
      if(i==n)
      {
          return 0;
      }
      if(dp[i][prev]!=-1){return dp[i][prev];}

      int take=INT_MIN;
      int not_take=0+f(i+1,prev,n,nums,dp);
      if(prev==i){
       take=1+f(i+1,i,n,nums,dp);
       not_take=0+f(i+1,i+1,n,nums,dp);
      }
      else if(nums[i]>nums[prev])
      {
        take=1+f(i+1,i,n,nums,dp);
      }

      return dp[i][prev]=max(take,not_take);
  }
};

```

