**Explanation**

In this apparoach we generally does not create a LIS but we create a temp vector which store all the elements which have to present in LIS then we return the length of that temp vector 

**Algo**

1 : Create a temprorary vector temp to store the elements of LIS
2 : push nums[0] into vector
3 : Traverse nums from 1 to n-1
4 : In loop check if (num[i] greater than temp.back)
     push nums[i] in vector
5 : else by binary search find the place for nums[i] in temp vector and replace it by nums[i]

6 : After completion of loop then return temp.size();


```
 int lengthOfLIS(vector<int>& nums) {
        ios::sync_with_stdio(0);
        cin.tie(NULL);
        int n = nums.size();
        if(n == 1)
        {
            return 1;
        }  
        vector<int> temp;   //The temp vector only carry the elements of LIS and not the LIS, Its only finding length
        temp.push_back(nums[0]);

        for(int i = 1;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(nums[i]>temp.back())
            {
                temp.push_back(nums[i]);
            }
            else
            {   //If the element is not greater than temp.back() then we simply place at equal element in temp or just next greater element 
                int idx = lower_bound(temp.begin(),temp.end(),nums[i])-temp.begin();
                temp[idx] = nums[i];
            }
        }
        return temp.size();
    }
	```

